Russians Rush to Leave as Sanctions Bite and Putin Clamps Down on Dissent Over Ukraine War
Some Russians are moving abroad amid fears Putin will declare martial law and close borders
A train from Russia arriving at the Tikkurila station near Helsinki. Bus and train tickets to Finland are sold out.
By Sune Engel Rasmussen in Vaalimaa, Finland and Alexander Osipovich in London | Photographs by Juuso Westerlund/INSTITUTE for The Wall Street Journal
March 9, 2022 12:50 pm ET

It isn’t just Ukrainians who are fleeing . Russians are leaving their homeland too.

One man, worried he might soon be unable to buy insulin for his wife, loaded two suitcases with medicine, two more with clothes and left with his spouse to stay with their daughter in Germany.
